Function Reference/wp suspend cache invalidation « WordPress Codex
-----------

Suspend cache invalidation.

Turns cache invalidation on and off. Useful during imports where you
don't wont to do invalidations every time a post is inserted. Callers
must be sure that what they are doing won't lead to an inconsistent
cache when invalidation is suspended.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_suspend_cache_invalidation( $suspend ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$suspend` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to suspend or enable cache invalidation
    Default: true

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(boolean)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   The current suspend setting

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.7](/Version_2.7 "Version 2.7")

Source File
-----------

`wp_suspend_cache_invalidation()` is located in
`wp-includes/functions.php`

